<!-- 3.1.23 -->
<div class='toload lemma'>
	<p><span class='envidentifier'>Lemma 3.1.23</span>
	Let $X$ be a topological space and $U$ an open set of $X$. Then
	<ol class='alphpar'>
		<li>
			If $A\in\operatorname{RO}(X)$ then $A\cap U\in\operatorname{RO}(U)$.
		</li>
		
		<li>
			The map
			<div class='equation'>\[
				\varphi_U:\operatorname{RO}(X)\to\operatorname{RO}(U),\qquad \varphi_U(A)=A\cap U
			\]</div>
			is order-preserving and surjective; The map $\zeta_U:A\mapsto \operatorname{int}_X(\operatorname{cl}_X(A))$ is an order-preserving right inverse to $\varphi_U$;
		</li>
		
		<li>
			$\varphi_U$ is an order isomorphism if and only if $U$ is dense in $X$.
		</li>
	</ol>
	</p>
</div>